### Get issues in repos the app has access to
GET http://localhost:3000/github/issues?installationId=YOUR_INSTALLATION_ID
Accept: application/json

### Create a bounty
POST http://localhost:3000/github/bounties
Content-Type: application/json
Accept: application/json

{
  "repo": "example-repo",
  "issue": 123,
  "amount": 100,
  "coin": "USDC",
  "chain_id": "1",
  "bountyOwner": "octocat"
}

### Get bounties by bountyOwner
GET http://localhost:3000/github/bounties?bountyOwner=octocat
Accept: application/json 